{{Quote|I've had many names throughout my life. The Warrior King, Master Khan, the most dangerous man on [[Earth]]. For years, I thought that was all I was meant to be. But when I met their [[Ying Li|mother]], everything changed.|Xu Wenwu to [[Katy Chen]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
'''Xu Wenwu''' (Mandarin: '''徐文武''') was a legendary and nearly mythical figure who rose to power after discovering a set of [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|mythical rings]], and founded the army known as the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]. Xu established himself as a powerful warlord who conquered kingdoms over the millennia, the rings' power gifting him immortality. In the modern-day, Xu had continued seeking power, finding the ancient city of [[Ta Lo]]. He fell in love with Ta Lo's gatekeeper, [[Ying Li]], and fathered [[Xu Shang-Chi]] and [[Xu Xialing]]. Despite swearing off violence to raise his family, Xu eventually reclaimed his rings when Ying was murdered at the hands of the [[Iron Gang]]. He trained Shang-Chi to be an assassin to avenge his wife's murder. However, Xu's two children would grow fearful of their father and eventually abandon him.

In the [[2013|21st Century]], Xu discovered that [[Aldrich Killian]] was able to recruit [[Trevor Slattery]] to impersonate Xu himself, giving him the '''Mandarin''' moniker, while also appropriating the legend of the Ten Rings. Enraged at Slattery's portrayal of him, Xu had him [[Kidnapping of Trevor Slattery|abducted]] and sentenced to imprisonment for tarnishing his name. Eventually, Xu would begin hearing his late wife's voice, urging him to free her from imprisonment in Ta Lo. Xu sought out his children to aid him, only for Shang-Chi and Xialing to reject his request, siding with [[Ying Nan]] to stop his army. Through his attempts to rescue his wife, Xu unintentionally unleashed the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]]. Xu sacrificed himself to protect Shang-Chi from the Dweller, passing the Ten Rings down to him, before the Dweller then drained his soul from Xu's body and killed him.

==Biography==
{{MD|Xu Wenwu (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
====Legendary Warlord====
{{Quote|He was a warrior king. Inspired generations of men through the Middle Ages, perhaps even further back in time.|[[Jackson Norriss]] to [[Trevor Slattery]]|Marvel One-Shot: All Hail the King}}
Around a thousand years ago, Xu Wenwu discovered [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|ten rings]] which had gifted him with unmatched power and immortality. Possessing the power of the rings, Xu soon became a powerful warlord and founded the organization, known as the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]].{{Ref|SCatLotTR}} Xu's past was shrouded in mystery, but his followers had described him as being an ancient warrior-king that has inspired generations of men since the [[Before 20th Century|Middle Ages]]. As the leader of the Ten Rings, Xu had become a myth to his followers, with only his most trusted men being aware that he really existed.{{Ref|MOSAHtK}}

===Leading the Ten Rings===
====Near-Global Conquest====
[[File:Leader of the Ten Rings.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu leading the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] into a battle]]
{{Quote|十環的傳說已經流傳了上千年。不論這個故事如何演變，它的主角永遠都是同一個人。有人說他的十環是火山口裡撿來的，還有人說是墓穴偷來的。它們給了他神一般的力量，也給了他長生不老的魔法。他本可藉著十環之力來懲惡揚善，但他想要的...只有征服。<ref>Translates from Mandarin to: "''The legend of the Ten Rings has been told for thousands of years. Every generation, the story grows. But at its center, there is always one man. Some say he found the rings in a crater or stole them from a tomb. They gave him the strength of a god, and the gift of eternal life. He could have used them for good. But all he wanted... was power."</ref>|[[Ying Li]] to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Having established his name as a legendary and feared warlord, Xu traveled across [[Asia]], building the power of the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] and conquering whatever lands he desired. On one instance, Xu would lead his army to a castle occupied by the {{WPS|Seljuk Empire}}, who stood in fear as Xu approached alone, on horseback. As a sea of arrows were fired at him, Xu unleashed the power of his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]], blocking the arrows as he charged forward.
[[File:Ten Rings Shield.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu blocks all the arrows with his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]]]]
With the power of his rings, Xu launched himself through the air, and landed in the middle of the defending army, as he swiftly used the power of his rings to obliterate his enemies. Keeping his foes at bay, Xu eventually launched a massive power strike from his rings, which blew through the opposing army and obliterated the gateway into the castle. Xu and his army were swiftly victorious, and had claimed the castle in the name of the Ten Rings.
[[File:Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings 36.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu watches [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] soldiers training]]
Xu and his army would take control of another facility, which would become the [[Ten Rings Headquarters]], where Xu would continue ruling over the Ten Rings, observing his army of soldiers training. Through the few hundred years, Xu would use his army's to continue building his power, as they assassinated their enemies and conquered more of the globe. However, despite the immense power he had gained, Xu would never be satisfied, and continued seeking more power.
[[File:Mandarin throws rings.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu uses his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] to defeat an army]]
Still desiring power, Xu led his Ten Rings into further battles. During one battle on a snow covered field, Xu found himself surrounded by another army, but with the power of his ten rings on his arms, Xu was able to easily overpower them, swiping the rings across the battle field and killing dozens of soldiers. Xu threw the rings at the army's wagons and uncovered their gold supplies, further building his power and wealth through the might of the ten rings.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Conflicts Across the Globe====
{{Quote|他打造了一支「十環軍團」。千百年來，他們掃蕩了世界每個角落。他們潛伏於暗中，顛覆各方政權，也改寫了歷史。憑藉著十環之力，他早已稱霸千年。但他...卻還不滿足。<ref>Translates from Mandarin to: "''He called his army The Ten Rings. Over the centuries, they spread into every corner of the world. They moved in the shadows, toppled governments and changed the course of history. He chased money and power for a thousand years. But he still wanted more.''"</ref>|[[Ying Li]] to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Under the leadership of Xu, the [[Ten Rings]] continued to conquer much of the world, expanding their reach beyond [[Asia]], as they took bases across [[India]] and [[Europe]]. As the decades went by, Xu found himself unbeatable, with his vast armies standing alongside him, as well as the power of his own [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|ten rings]], which he could use to destroy any armies that stood in his way. As Xu's strength grew, he allowed the Ten Rings to fall into the shadows, focusing on manipulating world events, rather than going into war.

With the wealth he had gathered from centuries of conquering Asia and claiming rival armies for himself, Xu's confidence and strength was unmatched. His soldiers became known in legend as some of the most feared in the globe. Xu and the Ten Rings continued moving with the times, upgrading their weaponry, as they continued to use [[Hooked-Swords]], but would electrify them for extra damage, while many soldiers would use guns and bombs to their advantage. However, Xu's only weapon remained his own ten rings, which he would never remove from his arms, ensuring he remained one of the most dangerous men in the world.

Xu led the Ten Rings into a global spy and terrorist organisation, as they focused on assassinations rather than all out war. During [[World War II]], Xu had one of his soldiers detonate a bomb within [[London]].{{Ref|SCatLotTR}} With their reach now expanding across the globe, Xu had a Ten Rings organisation established in [[Afghanistan]], and put [[Raza Hamidmi al-Wazar]] in charge of it.{{Ref|IM}} Due to their power, Xu gained many enemies across the globe, who sought to kill him and destroy the Ten Rings, including organisations such as the [[Iron Gang]], who mistakenly believed that due to their apparant silence, Xu and the Ten Rings were less of a threat.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====[[Duel in the Bamboo Forest]]====
[[File:Wenwu (1996).png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu flying back into his [[Ten Rings Headquarters|Headquarters]]]]
{{Quote|聽過大羅的傳說嗎？一個隱世的村莊，在那裡，神族的功法代代相傳。傳說中的神獸和古老的法術還都存在。我要找到這個地方。<ref>Translates from Mandarin to: "''Have you ever heard the legend of Ta Lo? A hidden village with mythical creatures and ancient magic. Where people practice a martial arts from the gods. I want to find it."</ref>|Xu Wenwu to [[Hui]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
In [[1996]], Xu, not yet fully satisfied with the power that he had amassed over the centuries, decided to seek out the village of [[Ta Lo]], said to contain various mythical beasts, to expand his powers. Xu returned to the [[Ten Rings Headquarters]], onboard his [[Ten Rings Helicopter|Helicopter]], while examining his books about Ta Lo and the creatures that were rumored to reside there.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}
[[File:MandarinReturnsToHeadquarters-DS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu and [[Hui]] discussing the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]]]
Upon landing at the headquarters, where the guards bowed to him, Xu was greeted by [[Hui]], who commented that he heard that their work in [[Afghanistan]] was going well, to which Xu noted that [[Raza Hamidmi al-Wazar]] had done good work at capitalizing on the instability in the region. Xu and Hui walked through the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] soldiers training, as Hui noted they were doing good work presenting Xu with pictures of dead men.
[[File:MandarinConfrontsHostage1-DS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu is delivered the [[Iron Gang]] leader]]
Hui then explained to Xu that they had successfully killed every member of the [[Iron Gang]], as they had been caught attempting to sell weapons in their territory without paying their dues to the Ten Rings. Xu was then presented with the new Iron Gang leader, who had been captured and was awaiting execution. Xu then calmly removed the leader's hood, as he questioned if he knew who he was, which the leader confirmed. 
[[File:MandarinConfrontsHostage2-DS.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu confronting the [[Iron Gang]] leader]]
Xu also questioned if the man knew the fate of men who stole from the Ten Rings, who which the leader noted that Xu's men had already killed his family, insisting that he should finish the job. In response, Xu grabbed the leader's throat and powered up his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]], only to instead tell the man to kill himself. With that, Xu ordered Hui to let the leader return home with no further punishment, before he returned to his office.{{Ref|SCatLotTRDS}}
[[File:Xu Wenwu (1996).png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu explaining his plans to find [[Ta Lo]]]]
Returning to the prospect that he had come to discuss, Xu had a meeting with Hui in his office, where he had explained his plan to find Ta Lo and claim their power for his own, with Hui promising that he would arrange for the Ten Rings to send out a scouting team to search the area for him as soon as possible. However, Xu's desire for the power that Ta Lo held, led him to insisting that they leave immediately to find it.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Duel Against Ying Li====
[[File:Trip to Ta Lo.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu and [[Hui]] witness the forest attack]]
{{Quote|你好像不知道我是誰。”<ref>Translates from Mandarin to: "''You don't know who you're talking to."</ref><br>“我不管你是誰。走吧，不要自找麻煩。<ref>Translates from Mandarin to: "''I don't care who you are. Turn around now, and I won't have to hurt you.''"</ref>|Xu Wenwu and [[Ying Li]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Once they tracked down the area, Xu and [[Hui]] were driven through a [[Bamboo Forest]] in their Jeeps, with Xu still closely examining his books for more details on the area. However, as they were driving, they realized that the forest was closing in around them, forcing their driver to attempt to flee.
[[File:Wenwu meets Ying Li.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu continues to search for [[Ta Lo]]]]
Once they reached a clearing, Xu realized that they were driving towards a cliff, as he used his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] to fling himself out of the car and land safely on the cliff edge. However, he was too late to save his allies, as Xu watched the car full to the bottom of the cliff, with Hui and his men still inside. Despite the loss, Xu continued on with his mission, going through the forest on foot.
[[File:Mandarin.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu preparing himself to battle [[Ying Li]]]]
Despite the forest itself having attacked him and his men, he made it to village's entrance, where he encountered a woman named [[Ying Li]], who guarded the entrance to [[Ta Lo]]. She and Xu engaged in a fight, where she displayed her own impressive combat skills, but the two immediately began to fall in love.
[[File:Wenwu defeated.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu is finally defeated by [[Ying Li]]]]
During the fight, Ying held her own against his Ten Rings, making Xu really impressed. However, much to his shock, Ying used her own powers to manipulate his Ten Rings so that they start to act against him, using his own powers against him. Ying temporarily took the ownership of all of his rings and turned it into a powerful energy ball to attack Xu, making him clash against a tree. However, before he would fall down hard on the ground and get seriously injured, Ying redirected him to the river using her powers, thereby saving his life.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

===Peaceful Life===
====Reunion with Ying Li====
[[File:Ying Li and Wenwu.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu having his picnic with [[Ying Li]]]]
{{Quote|[[Ying Li|She]] showed me a part of myself I didn't know was there. It was like I was seeing the world for the first time. She gave up everything so we could be together, and so did I.|Xu Wenwu to [[Katy Chen]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
A highly impressed Xu deeply fell in love for [[Ying Li]], not just the only woman to defeat him in a thousand years, but the only person. A lovestruck Xu returned to Ta Lo's gates again and again to meet Ying, where they would have dates at that same location and eventually fell in love. However, the villagers of [[Ta Lo]] would not accept Xu, fearing his past sins would have destroyed the village. As a result, Ying decided to leave Ta Lo with Xu.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Fleeting Peace====
[[File:Wenwu marries Ying Li.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu has wedding pictures taken with [[Ying Li]]]]
{{Quote|After all those years, I finally found something worth growing old for.|Xu Wenwu to [[Katy Chen]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
With [[Ying Li]] having chosen to leave [[Ta Lo]] in order to be with Xu, he in return chose to dedicate himself to a life of peace, focused on his love for her. As a result, Xu made the decision to aside his [[Ten Rings (Organization)|terrorist empire]] and even forsake the power of the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] in order to be with her, placing the rings in a box and accepting a limited life span in exchange for their relationship.
[[File:Wenwu holds Shang-Chi.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu holding his first born son, [[Xu Shang-Chi]]]]
Xu and Ying eventually married, settling down inside the [[Ten Rings Headquarters|compound]] that had once been the headquarters of the Ten Rings. The pair would have two children together, a son named [[Xu Shang-Chi]] and a daughter named [[Xu Xialing]]. For a time, Xu settled down with his family, believing he had finally found a purpose worthy to grow old for, with no desire to return to his former life as a war lord, instead enjoying nights of playing games and practicing martial arts as a family.
[[File:Xu Family.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu playing his games with his family]]
During this time, Xu and Ying had attempted to return to [[Ta Lo]] and live in peace there, however, the elders of Ta Lo, led by [[Guang Bo]] turned them away, claiming that Xu's history with the Ten Rings would destroy the peace of Ta Lo. Despite feeling insulted by this claim, Xu still made no retaliation, as he and Ying chose to remain in their home with their family, with Ying still teaching their children about the legends associated with Ta Lo, while Xu dedicated himself to peace.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====[[Attack on Ying Li|Losing His Love]]====
[[File:WenwuReturnsHome.png.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu discovering [[Ying Li]] has been killed]]
{{Quote|她說我是可以改變的，我也可以放下一切。可是她錯了。如果我當初沒有把它們摘下來，那些混蛋根本都不敢動手。我要他們付出代價。<ref>Translates from Mandarin to: "''She told me I could change, that I could leave my past behind, but she was wrong. If I hadn't taken them off, those men wouldn't have dared do this, and now they will pay for it."</ref>|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
One evening in [[2007]], Xu had left his [[Ten Rings Headquarters|home]], leaving [[Ying Li]] to look after their children, as she would train [[Shang-Chi]] in the ancient fighting style of [[Ta Lo]]. However, once Xu had returned to their home, he discovered a scene of destruction, with Shang-Chi and [[Xu Xialing]] standing among the chaos. Xu discovered that the [[Iron Gang]] had come searching for him to get revenge for his past actions, and had proceeded to murder Ying Li when they could not find him.
[[File:WenwuTalkstoShangChi.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu deciding to avenge [[Ying Li]]'s death]]
Xu was devastated by the loss of Ying, and returned to his room to grieve. Once Shang-Chi came to speak to his father, Xu was staring at his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] and noted that this never would have happened had he been wearing them, as the Iron Gang would not have dared to challenge him. With that, Xu decided to put the rings back on and avenge his wife's death.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

===Ten Rings Return===
====[[Massacre of the Iron Gang]]====
[[File:Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings 18.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu bringing [[Shang-Chi]] on his mission]]
{{Quote|血債...必須要血償。你願意幫爸爸嗎？<ref>Translates from Mandarin to: "''A blood debt, has to be paid by blood. Will you help me?"</ref>|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Having put the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] back on and chosen to return to his former life of violence and war, Xu began searching for the members of the [[Iron Gang]] who had invaded his [[Ten Rings Headquarters|home]] and murdered his wife. After tracking them down to a bar, Xu brought [[Shang-Chi]] along with him so that the latter could witness his father getting his payback for [[Ying Li]]'s death, walking hand in hand with Shang-Chi into the Iron Gang's bar, as customers looked on in surprise.
[[File:Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings 19.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu furiously attacks the [[Iron Gang]]]]
Letting go of Shang-Chi's hand, Xu stepped over to the table where the Iron Gang were enjoyed themselves, powered up his rings, and smashed his fist through their table. Before they could even react, Xu proceeded to mercilessly slaughter the Iron Gang and used the rings to launch them across the bar with incredible force, leaving Shang-Chi to watch in shock and then step aside as Xu used the power of his rings to launch one of the gang members into a glass wall next to him.
[[File:MandarinEvilStare.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu brutally kills the final gang member]]
With the final gang member lying seriously injureed by Shang-Chi's feet, Xu stepped over to him, pressing his foot hard down against his chest, and demanded to know where the [[Iron Gang Leader]] was so that he could kill him and avenge Ying Li. Unfortunately, the gang member insisted that he did not know, which Xu accepted. Having reestablished his reputation as a warrior to be feared, Xu proceeded to kill him with a blast of energy to the head, as Shang-Chi looked on in shock at the violence.
[[File:MandarinLeavingWithYoungShangChi.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu leaves the bar with [[Shang-Chi]]]]
With his revenge partly satisfied by this massacre of the Iron Gang's members, Xu turned his attention back towards Shang-Chi, as he asked if he was willing to help avenge his mother, insisting that a blood debt would have to be paid in blood. When Shang-Chi nodded yes to this, Xu took his hand and the two of them left the Iron Gang's bar behind, with Xu planning on how he would find the gang's leader and finally kill him, while also rebuilding his former power.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Training Shang-Chi====
[[File:Wenwu (Ten Rings HQ).png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu ordering to [[Shang-Chi]] to follow him]]
{{Quote|You have to strengthen your mind, along with your body. If you want [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|them]] to be yours one day, you have to show me you are strong enough to carry them.|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Although he avenged [[Ying Li]]'s death with the slaughter of the [[Iron Gang]], Xu was still left with an emptiness in his heart, so he chose to rededicate himself to the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] and wear his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Rings]] at all time. Xu also decided that he would have [[Shang-Chi]] trained to become a warrior for the Ten Rings, although he had also chosen to not have [[Xu Xialing]] trained, since Xu only wanted male warriors to fight in his armies.
[[File:Shang-Chi New image5.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu and [[Death Dealer]] train [[Shang-Chi]]]]
To assist in Shang-Chi's training, Xu recruited [[Death Dealer]], as he observed his son being trained to fight with the same foricity as the other Ten Rings warriors, training him with blades, as well as his own fists. Xu would also stand by and watch, as Shang-Chi was forced to punch a thick wooden bar repeatedly, with Death Dealer striking him with a stick if he began to relent due to the pain. Xu watched on, as Shang-Chi would punch the wooden bar for hours, leaving his knuckles bleeding. 
[[File:Wenwu and son.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu offering [[Shang-Chi]] some advice]]
Eventually, Xu approached Shang-Chi following hours of him punching the wooden bar and invited him to take a break. Retiring to his room, Xu cleaned the blood from his son's knuckles, promising that the pain would go away and he would eventually be stronger for it. As they were speaking, Xu noticed that Shang-Chi was looking at his Rings, as Xu noted that they had brought their family strength, and now Shang-Chi would have to prove himself to be strong enough to wear them himself.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Stark Industries Technologies====
[[File:Mandarin talks.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu hears of his men's failure]]
{{Quote|I understand you failed to obtain the [[War Machine Armor: Mark II|War Machine Armor]]. Explain why you should leave this room alive.|Xu Wenwu to [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings Agent]]|Iron Man 3 Prelude}}
In [[2008]], the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] struck a deal with [[Obadiah Stane]] which involved purchasing the illegal [[Stark Industries]] weapons. The Ten Rings ambushed the [[United States Air Force]] convoy in [[Afghanistan]] and kidnapped [[Tony Stark]], imprisoning him in their [[Ten Rings Base|base]], attempting to force him into making them weapons for them. However, Stark made a [[Iron Man Armor: Mark I|suit of armor]] and escaped. Stane later betrayed the Ten Rings and had [[Raza Hamidmi al-Wazar]] as well as multiple of his men killed.{{Ref|IM}}

Xu targeted Stark and attempted to have him assassinated by using [[Ivan Vanko]], sending his [[Ten Rings Agent|agent]] to arrange passage for Vanko to [[Monaco]], although this failed.{{Ref|IM2}} Over the next year, the Ten Rings suffered numerous defeats at the hands of [[Iron Man]], as Xu ordered his men to capture [[James Rhodes]] and his new [[War Machine Armor: Mark II|armor]]. Although Rhodes managed to defeat the Ten Rings, to Xu's frustration, his men managed to obtain a valuable information needed to take Iron Man down.<ref name="IM3P">''[[Iron Man 3 Prelude]]''</ref>

====2013 Copycat Attacks====
{{Quote|A [[Aldrich Killian|terrorist]] from [[United States of America|America]] needed a boogeyman to bring your country to its knees. So, he appropriated the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]. My Ten Rings. But because he didn't know my actual name, he invented a new one. Do you know the name he chose? The Mandarin. He gave his [[Trevor Slattery|figurehead]] the name of a chicken dish. And it worked. America was terrified. Of an orange.|Xu Wenwu to [[Katy Chen]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
In [[2013]], Xu became aware that [[Aldrich Killian]] had orchestrated the series of apparent terrorist attacks against the [[United States of America]] in order to cover up his illegal experiments,{{Ref|IM3}} inventing the moniker of the "Mandarin" who he claimed to be the leader of the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]],{{Ref|SCatLotTR}} which was an ancient [[China|Chinese]] war mantle, meaning "advisor to the King".{{Ref|MOSAHtK}} Xu was dismissive of the moniker, due to its association with mandarin oranges.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}} [[Trevor Slattery]], who portrayed "Mandarin", completely twisted his image, which absolutely infuriated him.

After Killian was defeated by [[Iron Man]], Slattery was arrested and imprisoned in the [[Seagate Penitentiary]], and Xu sent [[Jackson Norriss]] to break Slattery out of the prison and capture him. Disguised as a documentary filmmaker, Norriss successfully infiltrated the prison and [[Kidnapping of Trevor Slattery|abducted]] Slattery into Xu's custody.{{Ref|MOSAHtK}} Slattery was brought to Xu himself who was intended to kill him, however, in the last moments, he witnessed Slattery's actor performance and changed his mind. Xu instead decided to keep Slattery as his personal "court jester" and imprisoned him within the dungeons deep within his [[Ten Rings Headquarters|headquarters]], forcing him to perform monologues for his various guests and soldiers.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Completing Shang-Chi's Training====
[[File:Wenwu and death dealer.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu watches [[Shang-Chi]]'s combat skills]]
{{Quote|I trained you, so the most dangerous people in the world couldn't kill you.|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Once [[Shang-Chi]] was older, Xu observed him as his warriors were training his endurance, striking him with staffs, while Shang-Chi remained strong and barely reacted. Finally, Xu had a dozen of his [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] warriors attack his son with blades, only for Shang-Chi to prove himself as the superior warrior, being able to disarm all of his opponents with relative ease, coming out as the victor in the fight, much to the considerable satisfaction of Xu, who had been observing the entire clash, alongside [[Death Dealer]], with Xu confirming that Shang-Chi was ready to become a member of the Ten Rings.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Shang-Chi's First Mission====
[[File:Shangchi4k-movie-screencaps.com-1576.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu arranges [[Shang-Chi]]'s first mission]]
{{Quote|We found the [[Iron Gang Leader|man]] responsible for [[Attack on Ying Li|killing]] your [[Ying Li|mother]]. It is your right to finish this for both of us.|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
In [[2014]], following several years of searching, Xu finally discovered the location of the [[Iron Gang Leader|leader]] of the [[Iron Gang]], and set about exacting his revenge against this man. Since [[Shang-Chi]] had turned fourteen and was excelling at his training, Xu decided that he would send him out to assassinate the Iron Gang's leader, and thereby he would have avenged [[Ying Li]]'s death.
[[File:Shangchi4k-movie-screencaps.com-6705.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu giving [[Shang-Chi]] his instructions]]
Xu then met with Shang-Chi as his [[Ten Rings Helicopter|helicopter]] arrived to take him on the mission, with Xu handing his son a knife and telling his son that it was his right to avenge Ying Li's death for them. Xu had also expected this to be Shang-Chi's oppurtunity to prove himself to be a worth soldier within the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]. However, despite completing his mission and killing the man, Shang-Chi had failed to return to the [[Ten Rings Headquarters]], and chose to hide himself from Xu, and his future with the Ten Rings.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Adopting Razor Fist====
{{Quote|While I was on business in [[Romania]], I saw a [[Razor Fist|boy]] on the street who reminded me of you. He was standing on a box, juggling three balls with his one arm. I was so impressed, I adopted Mattias as my own.|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings - Deleted Scene}}
Xu traveled to [[Romania]] for business purposes. During his visit, he found a child named [[Mattias]] living on the streets who had lost his right hand, but was able to juggle three balls with his one remaining arm. Xu soon took a liking to Mattias since he had reminded him of [[Shang-Chi]], and decided to adopt him as his own son. Mattias soon became another of Xu's protégés, who quickly rose in the ranks to become one of the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]' top operatives.

Xu had a mechanized [[Razor Fist's Prosthetic Blade|Razor Blade]] to be implanted over Mattias' missing hand, and from that point on, Mattias dubbed himself "[[Razor Fist]]" and used the razor blade arm as his signature weapon. Xu found the name Razor Fist amusing and approved it, despite it technically being incorrect. Due to their mutual respect for one another, Xu would be willing to defend Razor Fist from insults, while Razor Fist followed Xu's orders without question.{{Ref|SCatLotTRDS}}

====Defection of Xu Xialing====
{{Quote|I always know where my children are.|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Following [[Shang-Chi]]'s disappearance, [[Xu Xialing]] eventually chose to defect from the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] as well, having used the tunnels underneath the dungeons within the [[Ten Rings Headquarters]] to sneak away without being seen. Xu used his vast resources to easily track down his children, but respected their decision to leave the Ten Rings and instead kept a close eye on them in their self-imposed exile without interference.

Xu observed as Shang-Chi changed his name to Shaun and moved to [[California]] to attempt to make a new life for himself, where he would become friends with [[Katy Chen]], although Xu would be disappointed to see his lack of ambition and only working as a valet. Meanwhile Xu would track Xialing to [[Macau]], where she would open the [[Golden Daggers Club]]. However, Xu always remained confident that one day his children would return to the Ten Rings.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

===Family Reunion===
====Locating his Children====
{{Quote|Did you get my postcard? The one with the [[Great Protector|dragon]]?"<br>"I know which one.|Xu Wenwu and [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Over the next few years, Xu began hearing a [[Dweller-in-Darkness|voice]] inside his head, which was the voice of [[Ying Li]], calling for Xu come rescue her. Believing the voice, Xu communicated with the voice and determined that Ying had not actually been killed by the [[Iron Gang]], and was instead being held captive in [[Ta Lo]]. As a result, Xu had determined that he would go to war with Ta Lo and rescue Ying, determined to reunite his family.

Knowing that the way into Ta Lo was almost impossible to navigate, Xu realized that the way to find the path would be to use the [[Eyes of the Dragon]], which would show him the [[Bamboo Forest|pathway]] into Ta Lo. However, Xu had realized that these eyes had been given to [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Xu Xialing]] before Ying's death. Xu ordered the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] to track down his children, tracking Shang-Chi down to [[California]], as he sent [[Razor Fist]] and [[Gao Lei]] to find him and reclaim the Eye, with them completing their mission following a duel with Shang-Chi.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====[[Attack on the Golden Daggers Club|Attack on the Golden Daggers]]====
[[File:MandarinReclaimsHisTenRings.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu stopping [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Death Dealer]]]]
{{Quote|I told my [[Ten Rings (Organization)|men]] they wouldn't be able to kill you if they tried. Glad I was right.|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Xu had then tracked [[Xu Xialing]] down to the [[Golden Daggers Club]], as he and his soldiers led an attack on the club in order to obtain her part of the [[Eyes of the Dragon]]. While [[Razor Fist]] and [[Death Dealer]] led the attack, chasing down Xialing and battling [[Shang-Chi]] who had come to aid his sister, Xu stayed back, until he and his soldiers had successfully captured Xialing and [[Katy Chen]], as he then found Shang-Chi battling Death Dealer.
[[File:Chi and Wenwu 1.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu being reunited with [[Shang-Chi]]]]
Stepping into the fight to break it up, Xu used his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] to grab Shang-Chi's arm and throw him back, revealing that he had already captured Xialing and Chen. Xu then told Shang-Chi that he had already told the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] that they would not have been able to kill him if they tried, noting that he was glad that Shang-Chi had proved him right by surviving. Xu then told Shang-Chi that it was time for them to return [[Ten Rings Headquarters|home]], as he and Shang-Chi rested their foreheads together and left the club.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Returning to Headquarters====
[[File:Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings 35.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu bringing his family to their [[Ten Rings Headquarters|home]]]]
{{Quote|I wanted you to find your [[Xu Xialing|sister]] so I wouldn't have to go through all this unnecessary violence to get you [[Ten Rings Headquarters|here]]. I hate being the bad guy all the time.|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Returning to his [[Ten Rings Helicopter|Helicopter]], Xu took his family and hostages back to their [[Ten Rings Headquarters|Headquarters]], as his army of [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] soldiers stood by and bowed to Xu as he arrived, as Xu looked to [[Shang-Chi]] to see his reaction to their greeting. Xu then allowed his children to explore their former home again, with Shang-Chi looking at his old training post, as [[Xu Xialing]] took [[Katy Chen]] to view her former bedroom.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}
[[File:MandarinLightingCandles.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu lighting joss sticks for [[Ying Li]]]]
As the day turned to evening, Xu took some time to look at his memorial to [[Ying Li]], where he lit joss sticks for her. Xu was then rejoined by Shang-Chi, as he handed him some joss sticks and told him that his mother would be happy that he had come home. Xu then questioned if Shang-Chi had gotten the postcard with the [[Great Protector]] on it from him, noting that he sent it so that Shang-Chi would be forced to seek out his sister without any unnecessary violence.
[[File:MandarinReunitedWithShangChi-DeletedScene.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu and [[Shang-Chi]] discuss their past]]
Xu claimed that he hated being the bad guy in his son's eye, to which Shang-Chi questioned how he had been able to find him in [[California]], to which Xu explained that he had always known where his children were. Xu went on to accuse Shang-Chi of bouncing from one family to the next, and meeting Chen in the [[United States of America]], who he called Shang-Chi's girlfriend, while they worked at the [[Fairmont San Francisco]] parking cars for rich guests.
[[File:MandarinTouchingShangChi-DeletedScene.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu inviting [[Shang-Chi]] to his dinner]]
Xu had then told Shang-Chi that he had given him ten years to live his life, while questioning where these years had gotten him, before telling him that it was time for Shang-Chi to take his place by his side, as the leader of the Ten Rings. However, Shang-Chi still insisted that this was not going to happen. In response, Xu simply told Shang-Chi that he reminded him of Ying, before noting that he must be hungry, and inviting him to join them for dinner.{{Ref|SCatLotTRDS}}

====Dinner with his Family====
[[File:MandarinBeCareful.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu discusses [[Trevor Slattery]]'s insults]]
{{Quote|I gave you ten years to live your life, and where did it get you? Now it's time for you to take your place by my side."<br>"That's not going to happen.|Xu Wenwu and [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Xu invited the group to join him for dinner, only to soon find tension between [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Razor Fist]], who had continued staring at each other. Although Xu insisted that they needed to stand down, since they were all on the same side now, Shang-Chi denied this was true. In response, Xu told Shang-Chi about his reaction to him running away, claiming that he had barely eaten or slept as a result of losing his son.

As he continued with his story, Xu explained that, while he was on a business trip in [[Romania]], he had encountered a young boy who reminded him of Shang-Chi, explaining that he had watched this boy standing on a box and juggling three balls with his one arm. Xu told Shang-Chi that he had adopted the boy as his own son, to which Razor Fist had also noted to Shang-Chi that his father gave him a home and a purpose with joining the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]].

While [[Xu Xialing]] noted that her father also gave him a [[Razor Fist's Prosthetic Blade|Razor Arm]], he insisted that it was called a Razor Fist, which Xialing and [[Katy Chen]] insisted did not make sense, due to the name being an oxymoron. However, seeing that Razor Fist was getting confused and frustrated, Xu insisted that they stop, noting that he could call his blade whatever he wanted. Following this, Razor Fist left the family and Chen alone to eat and talk.{{Ref|SCatLotTRDS}}

Xu asked Chen what her true [[China|Chinese]] name was, expressing the importance of their names. Xu went on to tell the group his true name, noting that the only person who used to use that name was [[Ying Li]]. Continuing with this thought, Xu told them about how [[Aldrich Killian]] had invented a name for him, by recruiting [[Trevor Slattery]] to portray him and appropritate of his Ten Rings to use it as a cover for Killian's terrorist actions. As they listened, Xu explained that this plan had worked, and that the [[United States of America]] had become terrified of a fake terrorist, named after a mandarin chicken dish as well as a mandarin orange.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Revealing the Secret Map====
[[File:Wenwu First Look.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu discusses [[Ying Li]]'s voice messages]]
{{Quote|Three days from now, we will rescue my [[Ying Li|wife]] from her prison and bring her home. This is why you're here. To help me bring her back to us."<br>"And what happens if they don’t let you open the [[Dark Gate|gate]]?"<br>"We'll burn the village to the ground.|Xu Wenwu and [[Xu Xialing]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Xu explained to his guests that [[Ying Li]] had been seemingly speaking with him, which [[Shang-Chi]] had refused to believe, leading to Xu promising to prove it to them. Xu brought them all into his office, as he explained that he had been working there when he heard the [[Dweller-in-Darkness|voice]] of his late wife, claiming that she was still alive and had actually been imprisoned within [[Ta Lo]], as she begged for Xu to come and save her. However, Shang-Chi and [[Xu Xialing]] remained unconvinced, insisting that their mother was dead.

Determined to prove this to them, Xu took his family to a sculpture of the [[Great Protector]], where he placed the [[Eyes of the Dragon]], causing water to be shot out around them, only to freeze in time, much to the amazement of Shang-Chi. As they watched, the water then fell on the ground and created a map, which Xu explained was the secret pathway into Ta Lo. Xu told Shang-Chi and Xialing that he intended to follow this path and attack Ta Lo, with the intention of rescuing his wife from them.

Despite him showing that he had the support of the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] behind him, as his warriors held up their [[Hooked-Swords]] in salute of Xu, Shang-Chi insisted that they could not attack Ta Lo, claiming that there was no way that their mother was alive, and Xu would be committing genocide for no reason. Enraged by this, Xu proceeded to use his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] to throw Shang-Chi, Xialing and [[Katy Chen]] to the ground, ordering [[Razor Fist]] to take them into their prison cells while they prepared for war.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Preparing for War====
[[File:MandarinRazorFistWatchingScreens.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu watches as his [[Shang-Chi|chil]][[Xu Xialing|dren]] escape him]]
{{Quote|They'll come back once I bring [[Ying Li|her]] home. Prepare the men for war.|Xu Wenwu to [[Razor Fist]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
As Xu had been watching the monitors of the [[Ten Rings Headquarters]], he witnessed [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Xu Xialing]] managing to steal a [[Razor Fist's Car|Car]] from their garage and escaping from the compound, having managed to get out of their cell, taking [[Katy Chen]] and [[Trevor Slattery]] with them. As Xu watched his children escaping from him, he was rejoined by [[Razor Fist]], as he instructed him to prepare for their mission, which Razor Fist had agreed to.
[[File:Xu Wenwu's Office.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu studies ahead of his upcoming battle]]
Xu then prepared for the upcoming battle by wearing his armor, before sitting in his office, studying his books on [[Ta Lo]] in order to ensure that he knew everything possible about the [[Ta Lo Armed Forces]] before he went into battle against them. As he read, Xu heard the [[Dweller-in-Darkness|voice]] of [[Ying Li]] in his head, calling out for him to rescue her, as he turned to see the vision of Ying and Xialing sitting together and smiling at him. The voice and vision further enforced Xu's determination to rescue his late wife from Ta Lo, as he remained convinced that this vision was real and she could be saved.
[[File:Shangchi4k-movie-screencaps.com-6093.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu giving [[Razor Fist]] his instructions]]
Xu was then snapped back to reality once Razor Fist had arrived outside his office, and informed him that the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] were now ready for the mission to attack Ta Lo, to which Xu confirmed that the pathway would be open by dawn, at which time they would begin the assault. Razor Fist then agreed to prepare their squad of Jeeps for the mission to attack, as he left Xu to continue studying all his books and preparing to battle the people of Ta Lo, and to rescue Ying from their custody.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====[[Battle of Ta Lo]]====
[[File:Xu Wenwu (Ta Lo).png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu leading the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] into [[Ta Lo]]]]
{{Quote|You've spent your entire life afraid. Always running, always hiding. You were there when [[Iron Gang|they]] came for [[Ying Li|her]], and you did nothing. You stood at a window and watched her die!|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Using the guide given to him by the [[Eyes of the Dragon]], Xu was able to lead his soldiers into [[Ta Lo]], as they drove their Jeeps into the other dimension, until they eventually found their path was blocked by the villagers of Ta Lo. Once his soldiers had stepped out and stood their ground against the villagers, Wenwu stepped forward, finding that [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Xu Xialing]] had betrayed him and joined the villagers against him.
[[File:MandarinPreBattle3.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu demands that [[Ta Lo]] surrender to him]]
Xu attempted to convince his children that [[Ying Li]] was being held behind the [[Dark Gate]] and he was there to rescue her, although Shang-Chi had insisted that this was not true. Xu was also challenged by [[Ying Nan]] and [[Guang Bo]], who insisted that they were not hiding his late wife, with Bo claiming that they had turned Xu away from Ta Lo years earlier, because the crimes of his past would have destroyed their land, which angered Xu, as he called Bo a young man and threatened him.
[[File:MandarinGivingOrder.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu orders the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] begin their attack]]
Despite being told that he would not be honouring his wife's legacy if he proceeded with the attack, Xu still demanded to be allowed to pass, which Ying Li refused, as the [[Ta Lo Armed Forces]] readied their weapons, with [[Razor Fist]] preparing his soldiers to defend Xu, with Ten powering up his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] in readiness. Eventually, Xu was forced to accept that his children would not join him, as he turned to Razor Fist and ordered him to lead the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] in an attack against the villagers.
[[File:MandarinThreatened.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu is challenged to fight by [[Ying Nan]]]]
Xu then stood by and watched the Ten Rings firing their [[Electrified Crossbows]] at the villagers before engaging them in a battle with their [[Hooked-Swords]]. As chaos broke out across the village, Xu remained focused on the Dark Gate and calmly marched through the battle. Before he could reach the village's temple, Xu was stopped and challenged by Ying, who was wielding a [[Dragon Scale Staff]], as she was determined not to allow him to open the gates, claiming that [[Dweller-in-Darkness|what]] was there would destroy them all.
[[File:MandarinShangChiStandOff.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu being challenged by [[Shang-Chi]]]]
Xu remained uninterested in this fight, as he only wished to find his wife, and before Ying could attack him, [[Death Dealer]] leapt in between them attacked Ying, throwing his [[Death Dealer's Daggers|daggers]] at her and forcing her to be distracted and allowing Xu to continue his march towards the Dark Gate. With the battle happening around him, Xu was spotted stepping into the village temple by Shang-Chi, who chased after him, with Xialing remaining focused on battling the Ten Rings army while Shang-Chi could deal with their father.
[[File:WenwuConfronts.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu calmly confronting [[Shang-Chi]]]]
Stepping inside the village's temple, Xu bowed and prayed before the image of Ying, until he was found and confronted by Shang-Chi. Once again, Shang-Chi desperately attempted to convince his father that his mother was not behind the gates, which Xu refused to listen to. Xu then attempted to throw his son off balance by insulting him, only for Shang-Chi to insist that he was no longer afraid of him, which Xu denied.
[[File:Mandarin (Ta Lo).png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu begins to fight against [[Shang-Chi]]]]
The father and son then began fighting each other, with Xu unleashing his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] against Shang-Chi, who defended himself with his [[Dragon Scale Staff]]. Xu insulted his son saying that he spent his entire life afraid - always running and always hiding. However, eventually Xu managed to launch himself into the air and land a kick to Shang-Chi's head, knocking him to the floor, while also insulting his son by reminding him of how he had hidden in fear when the [[Iron Gang]] had come to their [[Ten Rings Headquarters|home]] and murdered Ying, as Shang-Chi watched.
[[File:Xu Wenwu vs. Shang-Chi.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu eventually defeating [[Shang-Chi]]]]
However, rather than this stopping Shang-Chi, this resulted in him becoming enraged as Shang-Chi attacked him father, forcing the fight to leave the temple. Once they made distance between one another, Xu began firing his rings at Shang-Chi, who was able to block the attacks with his staff before continuing to fight his father. As Shang-Chi and Xu continued to fight, Shang-Chi pointed out that he and Xialing need Xu to be the comforting parent after Ying's death, but instead chose revenge over his family, and even if he managed to get his mother back, why would she take him back. In fury, Xu immediately ended the battle by striking Shang-Chi with the full force of the rings, launching him into the lake with incredible force.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

====Showdown with Shang-Chi====
[[File:MandarinMovingTheTenRings.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu begins to attack the [[Dark Gate]]]]
{{Quote|I have to save [[Ying Li|her]]. She's calling to me."<br>"I wish that were true. Dad, please. Your family needs you.|Xu Wenwu and [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
With nobody standing in his way, Xu launched himself through the air with the power of his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]], and landed before the [[Dark Gate]]. As Xu stepped to the gates and touched the [[Dragon Scale]], he heard the voice of [[Ying Li]] in his head once again, calling to him to rescue her. In response, Xu then powered up his rings and proceeded to punch the Dark Gate with all of his strength, causing shockwaves to begin shifting the scales.

As Xu continued to punch the gates, he transferred all ten rings onto one arm, so he could punch with more strength, but failed to noticed that the shifting of the scales was causing [[Soul Eaters]] to be freed from the gates, which then flew back to the village. Eventually, while Xu continued punching the gate, the [[Great Protector]] flew out of the lake to protect the villagers from the Soul Eaters that Xu had inadvertently unleashed upon them.

With the Great Protector battling the Soul Eaters, Xu was then knocked off his feet by the return of [[Shang-Chi]], who kicked his father away from the gate and stood against him. Once again, Shang-Chi insisted that Ying was not back there, although Xu protested that he had to save her, blind to the creatures that he was unleashing. To stop his father, Shang-Chi then demonstrated the fighting style of [[Ta Lo]], as Xu prepared for the fight.

The father and son had then continued their previous battle, with Shang-Chi now using the same fighting style as his mother, which [[Ying Nan]] had taught him, to get the upper hand over Xu. Despite his son doing better in this clash, Xu was still able to use the power of the rings against him, only for Shang-Chi to eventually manage to use his control of the air to catch five of the rings in mid-air, giving him control over them.
[[File:Mandarin vs Shang-Chi.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu battles [[Shang-Chi]] for the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]]]]
Xu and Shang-Chi then battled for control over the rings, eventually finding themselves locked in a pull of power between the rings, with each using five of the rings to attempt to pull them away from the other. Determined to end the battle, Xu then proceeded to launch his remaining five rings at Shang-Chi with all of his power, causing a large explosion, while Xu fell to the ground hard, believing that he had defeated Shang-Chi.
[[File:Wenwu Braces himself for defeat..png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu braces himself for defeat]]
However, to Xu's amazement, Shang-Chi stepped forward with the power of all ten rings under his control. Xu then stood by helplessly, as Shang-Chi used the same power of his mother to increase the power of the rings, preparing to fire a deadly blast of energy at Xu, which would undoubtedly kill him. Despite having the opportunity to kill his father however, Shang-Chi instead dropped the rings at his feet, demonstrating his power.
[[File:WRRP.png|{{AltFloat}}|Xu realizes he has been deceived]]
As they stood against each other, Xu insisted that he had to save Ying, only for Shang-Chi to once again insist that, while he wished it was true, his mother was not back there. However, before they could continue to attempt to find a peaceful resolution, they witnessed the Dark Gate being destroyed, as the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]] burst through, having gained enough power. Xu could only look on in horror, as he realized that he had been deceived.
[[File:MandarinWenwuDeathScene.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Xu is killed by the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]]]]
With the Dweller free, it turned to attack Xu and Shang-Chi, only for Xu to reclaim the rings and use their power to throw them both out of the way. However, this caused Xu to briefly turn his back to the Dweller, who snatched him from the ground with its tentacles and began sucking the lifeforce from his body. Knowing he could not be saved, Xu looked down at his son, reminiscing on times he spent with Shang-Chi, from his adulthood to when he was only an infant, and bequeathed the ten rings to him before the Dweller consumed his soul and killed him.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

===Legacy===
====Ten Rings' Leadership====
{{Quote|If my dad won't let me into his [[Ten Rings (Organization)|empire]], I'm gonna build my own.|[[Xu Xialing]] to [[Katy Chen]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
Upon obtaining the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]] following Xu's death, [[Shang-Chi]] was able to kill the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]], avenging Xu's death. The following night Xu's death was honored alongside [[Ying Li]], and all the others who lost their lives during the battle, with both Shang-Chi and [[Xu Xialing]] having come to terms with their father and forgiven him despite all he did. Shang-Chi kept the rings for himself but opted to use them more responsibly, while Xialing claimed she would finish dismantling the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]. Instead, Xialing took over Xu's position as the new leader of the Ten Rings intending to continue her father's work, while implementing major reforms.{{Ref|SCatLotTR}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
*'''[[Ten Rings]] Empowerment''': The [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] granted Xu with a variety of superhuman abilities, including enhanced strength, durability, speed, agility, stamina, reflexes, nigh-immortality, and the ability to manipulate the rings at will. When the rings were used by Xu, they generated an aura of blue, purple, and transparent energy currents around them while an aura of blue and purple dim light running through the veins of his body, whereas they glowed orange and golden while being used by [[Shang-Chi]].
**'''Superhuman Strength''': [[File:Wenwu breaking down the Dark Gate.png|thumb|250px|Xu breaking down the [[Dark Gate]]]] Xu's physical strength was enhanced to superhuman level by the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]], numerous times stronger than any normal human being. The enhanced strength granted by the rings was proportional to how many rings Xu was wearing at once, he usually kept five rings on each arm to evenly distribute his strength enhancement but could double the power of his punches by moving all rings to a single arm. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he used the rings to fling a soldier high up through the air before smashing him to the ground, generating a shockwave around him, and send many soldiers flying away with ease. During his expedition to find [[Ta Lo]], he easily break open the door of his jeep to escape when it was driving towards the cliff. He was able to match [[Ying Li]]'s strength, who was empowered by the [[Great Protector]], generating a slight grey shockwave when blocking and countering each others blows. He was able to effortlessly slam both his son and daughter to the ground when both of them disagreed the decision on attacking Ta Lo, strong enough to cause [[Shang-Chi]] flipping in the air several times before hitting the ground. During the [[Massacre of the Iron Gang|Massacre]] of the [[Iron Gang]], he was able to punch a member of the Iron Gang several meters away, killing him instantly, and smash through their table with his fist, breaking it in half. He was also able to easily launch one of the member across the bar with considerable force, and then swiftly slam away one member for several meters towards another member, causing them to crash against a wall with incredible force, killing them both. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo|Battle]] of [[Ta Lo]], Xu was able to easily push [[Shang-Chi]] several meters back, land a kick to his head which knocking him to the ground with some bruise on his forehead, land a kick to his chest which knocking him back, and charge at and push him far away back, leaving the temple and crashed into a grassland with cuts on his cheek. He was able to easily hold back Shang-Chi [[Dragon Scale Staff]], with him being unable to pull his staff out of his father's grip. He was even able to slightly shake the dragon scale on the [[Dark Gate]] when punching it, strong enough to generate shockwaves with each punch which slightly shifted the scales and caused debris to fall, weakened the magic inside them. By transferring all of the Ten Rings into a single arm, they greatly augmented his physical strength, allowing him to completely shake the dragon scale on the [[Dark Gate]] when punching it, generating a huge shockwave with each punch and further weakened the magic inside them, causing Soul Eaters to be freed from the gates as the scales shifted considerably. He was able to punch [[Shang-Chi]] away for several meters even after he was empowered by the [[Great Protector]]. During the battle against Shang-Chi who gained control over five of his rings, Xu was even able to successfully block his powerful kick which had enhanced its strength by wearing the rings on his leg, generating a huge shockwave around them, and had enough strength to push Shang-Chi back several meters away through the air with considerable force.
**'''Superhuman Durability''': Xu's durability was enhanced by the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]], making him very resistant to physical and energy damage, as well as being able to withstand falling from immense heights that would definitely kill a normal human. During his expedition to find [[Ta Lo]], Xu was able to withstand and survive the car crash without any injury, and later he was able to easily withstand being hit and kicked by [[Ying Li]], and survived being hit by an energy ball projected at him by her using his own rings and then crashed against a tree with considerable force, all without any noticeable injury. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo|Battle]] of [[Ta Lo]], he was able to easily withstand being hit by [[Shang-Chi]] with his [[Dragon Scale Staff]], with no injuries and keep fighting afterwards. He was able to easily withstand attacks from Shang-Chi even after he was empowered by the [[Great Protector]], being able to withstand a kick launch at him with considerable force after dropping down from a very high position with no injuries, and withstand being launched far way through the air by Shang-Chi with substantial force. He was even able to survive falling from a considerable height without wearing the rings, as he used all of his rings to attack Shang-Chi, with no noticeable injuries.
**'''Superhuman Speed''': Xu's speed was enhanced by the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]], allowing him to run and move at great levels of speed. He was fast enough to go toe-to-toe with [[Ying Li]], who was empowered by the [[Great Protector]], and even being able to go toe-to-toe with [[Shang-Chi]], who was empowered by the Great Protector and later the Ten Rings.
**'''Superhuman Agility''': [[File:Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings 49.jpg|thumb|250px|Xu leaping towards [[Ying Li]]]] Xu's agility was enhanced by the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]], allowing him to coordinate his body with perfect balance, equilibrium, flexibility, and dexterity, as well as leaping great distances and heights with precision. Xu used the rings as a means of propulsion to launch himself into the air then land safely by shooting the rings towards the ground in order to break a fall. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he used the rings to launch himself several meters high up into the air and again to safely land on the ground. During his expedition to find [[Ta Lo]], he easily leap out of his jeep mid-air and land safely on the cliff edge when it was flinging towards a cliff. During his fight against [[Ying Li]], Xu used the rings to launch him several meters forward to attack her, and again but without shooting out the rings. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo|Battle]] of [[Ta Lo]], Xu easily flipped several meters high in the air to kick at [[Shang-Chi]], and later he used the rings to launch himself several hundred meters through the air, flying across the lake between the village and the mountain, and again to safely land before the [[Dark Gate]]. He was also able to jump several meters up to attack Shang-Chi, and use the rings to safely land on ground after being launched far away through the air by Shang-Chi who had empowered by the [[Great Protector]]. During the battle against Shang-Chi who gained control over five of his rings, Xu was able to maintain balance mid-air and land back on the ground after being fling away several meters by him, and jump up for a considerable height without shooting out the rings to attack [[Shang-Chi]]. He used the rings to launch himself several meters away while saving Shang-Chi in the process, successfully dodged the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]] crashing at them.
**'''Superhuman Stamina''': Xu's stamina was enhanced by the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]], allowing him to exert himself at peak capacity for long periods of time without tiring or showing any sign of fatigue. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he was able to fight against their entire army single-handedly for an extended period of time without tiring. During his fight against [[Ying Li]], he was able to fight against her for a long period of time without any sign of fatigue. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo]], Xu was able to fight against [[Shang-Chi]] for an exceedingly long period of time without tiring.
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': [[File:Wenwu and Shang-Chi.png|thumb|250px|Xu catching [[Shang-Chi]]'s [[Dragon Scale Staff|Dragon Staff]]]] Xu's reflexes were enhanced by the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]], allowing him to react and dodge objects traveling at high speeds. During the fight against [[Ying Li]], his reflexes were sharp and fast enough to dodge or block her rapid attacks with ease, and effortlessly dodge a rich hat hurled to him at high speed. During the [[Massacre of the Iron Gang|Massacre]] of the [[Iron Gang]], he used the rings to block a pistol and a shotgun fired at him at point-blank range by the members of Iron Gang with ease. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo|Battle]] of [[Ta Lo]], Xu was able to effortlessly dodge and block [[Shang-Chi]] attacked with his [[Dragon Scale Staff|staff]], and even catch it from behind without even looking. After Shang-Chi was empowered by the [[Great Protector]] and later the Ten Rings, Xu's reflexes were sharp and fast enough to dodge or block his rapid and powerful attacks at close range with ease. He was also able to dodge the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]] crashing at him and Shang-Chi while saving his son in the process.
**'''Nigh-Immortality''': The [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] stop Xu from ageing as long as they are worn, as well as preventing him to die from natural causes, such as earthly infections, diseases, and disorders, making him near-immortal. He was still in his prime despite being more than a thousand years old. However, the rings did not grant him true immortality as they could not protect the user from fatal injuries or supernatural causes of death, as seen when his soul was consumed by the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]] and killed him.
**'''Weapon Calling''': [[File:Wenwu recalls the rings.png|thumb|250px|Xu recalling the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] to his arms]] The [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] obeyed Xu calling as though they were driven by a form of intelligence and self-awareness. He was able to telepathically control and use them as weapons in various ways to attack his opponents, and would return to him whenever he wants. However, [[Shang-Chi]] was able to take control of the rings away from him by using the unique martial arts practiced in [[Ta Lo]] to redirect their energy, and later even took control of all the rings.
**'''Energy Manipulation''': Xu could control and manipulate a magic energy field emitted by the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] at will, generating an aura of blue, purple, and transparent energy currents. He could use them for a variety of purposes, such as creating an energy barrier, shooting the rings towards the ground to launch himself high up into the air and again to safely land on the ground, firing them individually or together as high-powered projectiles, shooting blasts of energy, extending the rings as energy chain to use as a whip, projecting energy blasts, and blocking or deflecting attacks from opponents.
***'''Energy Projection''': [[File:MandarinShootingEnergyBlast.png|thumb|250px|Xu shooting the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] at [[Ying Li]]]] Xu could shoot the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] individually or together as energy projectiles. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he shot the rings to attack several soldiers at once, knocking them down and strong enough to shatter their armor. He later shot the rings to overpower an entire army with ease during a battle across a snow covered forest. During his fight against [[Ying Li]], he shot one of his rings at her, breaking the rocks behind her after she dodged it, and shot five rings at her mid-air while launching towards her, penetrating a tree's trunk after she dodged them, and shot one of his rings at her again when attacking her. He later charged his rings to enhance the energy in them and then shot all of the rings at her. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo]], Xu shot his rings one at a time consecutively at [[Shang-Chi]], and later shot five rings at him to the chest at point-blank range, breaking his staff in half, and shot five rings at him again with extreme force, launching him very far away into the lake at high speed, generating a massive wave and leaving him in an unconscious state. He shot one of his rings at [[Shang-Chi]] again after he was empowered by the [[Great Protector]]. After Shang-Chi gained control over five of his rings, Xu shot his remaining five rings to attack him while simultaneously deflecting his attacks, and smash the rings to the ground with considerable force and launch them towards Shang-Chi, cracking the ground and generating small shockwaves along the path of the rings, and shot them at him from underneath the ground, sent him flying upwards for a considerable height, and then shot all five rings at him after jumping very high up into the air with substantial force, causing him to crash into the ground and generate an immensely huge shockwave. Moreover, Xu could shoot the rings towards the ground to launch himself high up into the air and again to safely land on the ground. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he shot the rings towards the ground and launch himself several meters high up into the air and again to safely land on the ground, generating powerful shockwaves in both of the processes which knocked down the soldiers nearby. During his fight against Ying, Xu shot two rings on each arms to launch himself several meters forward to attack her. Xu could also launch himself high up into the air without shooting out the rings by projecting energy towards the ground. During his fight against [[Ying Li]], he used them to launch himself several meters forward to attack her. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo|Battle]] of [[Ta Lo]], he shot all of his rings towards the ground and launch himself several hundred meters through the air, flying across the lake between the village and the mountain, and again to safely land before the [[Dark Gate]]. He later shot all of his rings towards the ground to launch himself several meters away while saving [[Shang-Chi]] in the process, successfully dodged the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]] crashing at them.
***'''Energy Blast''': [[File:Wenwu kills a man.png|thumb|250px|Xu kills gang member with energy blast]] Xu could use the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] to project an energy blast. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he used all of his rings to project a massive energy blast that was powerful enough to go through the entire opposing army that was in its path, sending numerous soldiers flying away upon impact and completely destroyed the gateway of the castle. He later used five of his rings to project an energy blast to flip over a horse cart carrying lots of gold during a battle across a snow covered forest. Xu could also shoot blasts of energy out of his arm without shooting out the rings. During his fight against [[Ying Li]], he shot an energy blast at her after launching towards her. During the [[Massacre of the Iron Gang]], he shot an energy blast at a member of the Iron Gang, causing him to fly away and crash through a window, and killing another member by shooting an energy blast directly into his head at point-blank range. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo|Battle]] of [[Ta Lo]], he used five of his rings to project an energy blast at [[Shang-Chi]] with considerable force.
***'''Chain Creation''': [[File:MandarinAncientBattle.png|thumb|250px|Xu uses the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] as a battle chain]] Xu could extend the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] as energy chain to use as a whip. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he used five of his rings to form an energy chain to strangle a soldier and fling him high up through the air before smashing him to the ground, and later even used all of his rings to form a longer and more powerful energy chain to attack many soldiers at once, strong enough to send them flying away upon impact. He later used five of his rings to form an energy chain to overpower an entire army with ease during a battle across a snow covered forest. During his fight against [[Ying Li]], Xu used all of his rings to form energy chain to attack her, managed to briefly subdue her by tying them to her arm and pulling her towards him. He used five of his rings to form an energy chain to bind [[Shang-Chi]]'s arm and throw him several meters back when he was about to kill the [[Death Dealer]]. During the [[Massacre of the Iron Gang|Massacre]] of the [[Iron Gang]], he used five of his rings to form an energy chain to strangle a member of the Iron Gang and easily launch him across the bar, crashing against a glass wall which severely injured him. During the [[Battle of Ta Lo|Battle]] of [[Ta Lo]], he used five of his rings to form an energy chain to attack [[Shang-Chi]]. He also used five of his rings on each arm to form two energy chains to safely land on the ground after being launched far away through the air by Shang-Chi. After Shang-Chi gained control over five of his rings, Xu used the remaining five rings to form an energy chain to fight against him. The rings were strongly held together by a magic energy field, when they battled for control over the rings, neither of them could break each others energy whip with each using five of the rings to attempt to pull them away from the other, which locked in a pull of power between the rings and ending up in stalemate.
***'''Force-Field Generation''': [[File:Wenwu shield.png|thumb|250px|Xu blocks all the arrows with his [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|rings]]]] Xu could use the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] to create an energy barrier. During the battle against the Seljuk Empire, he spun the rings around himself at high speed to create a large energy barrier while riding his horse, blocking all the arrows as he charged forward. During the [[Massacre of the Iron Gang]], he used the rings to create a small energy barrier, durable enough to withstand a pistol and a shotgun fired at him at point-blank range by members of Iron Gang.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|Are you planning to stop me all by yourself?|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:Wenwu vs. Ying Li.png|thumb|250px|Xu fighting against [[Ying Li]]]] As the leader of the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]], Xu was an extremely skilled and formidable hand-to-hand combatant and martial artist, with centuries of training and combat experience, making him one of the most powerful and best fighters on the planet. His fighting style resembled the Hung Gar style of Kung Fu. He had defeated and killed many enemies in his lifetime. Xu also trained his son [[Shang-Chi]] into one of the most dangerous martial artist in the world. He repeatedly defeated numerous opponents with ease and held his own well against [[Ying Li]] despite her great martial arts skills being complimented by her aerokinesis. When fighting Shang-Chi, Xu proved to be a superior fighter, being able to easily gain the upper hand on and decisively defeat his son while he was using a [[Dragon Scale Staff]], though Xu was using the rings. He was able to knock him down repeatedly and swiftly reverse Shang-Chi's brief dominance, breaking his staff and sending him into the ocean. Even after Shang-Chi acquired his aerokinesis, Xu was still able to fight evenly with him, managing to deliver multiple blows and counter Shang-Chi's moves, ultimately ending the fight in a standstill.
*'''Chain Mastery''': Xu was extremely skilled in using a chain for combat, being able to use the Ten Rings to conjure an energy whip. He was able to easily take down multiple enemies with a single swing and evenly match against [[Shang-Chi]] when they are both using the Ten Rings to conjure a whip during the [[Battle of Ta Lo]].
*'''Master Marksman''': Xu was an extremely skilled marksman. He could launch his rings with force and accuracy.
*'''Master Acrobat''': [[File:Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings 58.jpg|thumb|250px|Xu kicking at [[Shang-Chi]]]] Xu was highly skilled acrobat and gymnast due to years of training and experience. His acrobatic abilities was further enhanced by the powers of the Ten Rings. He was able to perform highly acrobatic feats when fighting against [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Ying Li]].
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': Living for thousands of years, Xu had garnered immense amounts of knowledge by pure experience, allowing him to effectively rule the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|terrorist organization]] for thousands of years.
*'''Master Tactician''': Xu somewhat a highly skilled, effective tactician and leader, successfully lead his own army with great efficiency and conquered many lands.
{{Quote|Have you been practicing your English?|Xu Wenwu to [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
*'''Bilingualism''': Xu was fluent in his native Mandarin, as well as English.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
{{Quote|How long did your dad have [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|them]] before he gave them to you?"<br>"Um... About a thousand years.|[[Captain Marvel]] and [[Shang-Chi]]|Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings}}
*'''[[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]]''': [[File:Rings blue.png|thumb|250px|Xu wielding the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] on his arms]] Xu allegedly acquired the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|Ten Rings]] from a crater or stole them from a tomb. The rings drastically increased his strength and lifespan, and he could also wield them in a manner similar to a whip or launch them as projectiles and remotely return them to his arms. They also glowed blue on his person, whereas they glowed orange while being used by [[Ying Li]] or [[Shang-Chi]]. Xu used the power from these rings to conquer much of [[Asia]], with his army of the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]], becoming a feared warrior. However, Xu gave up the rings for several years, once he had fallen in love with Ying, only choosing to take them back following her death. Xu would use the power of these rings in a final effort to save his wife, believing her to be behind the [[Dark Gate]], although this was a deception by the [[Dweller-in-Darkness]]. During his duel with Shang-Chi, who was attempting to stop him, Xu inadvertently unleashed the Dweller from it's imprisonment, as Xu passed the ten rings down to Shang-Chi moments before the Dweller took his soul and life.

===Other Equipment===
*'''Armor''': As the leader of the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]], Xu would march into battle wearing a full suit of protective armor, despite him using the [[Ten Rings (Weapons)|ten rings]] to create protective shields that sheltered him from incoming arrows. Many centuries later, Xu donned a protective set of black and blue armor for the [[Battle of Ta Lo]]. The sleeves were short enough for him to wear his rings. and the belt featured the symbol of his organization.

===Vehicles===
*'''[[Ten Rings Helicopter]]''': Xu and the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]] owned a helicopter which he used to pick up [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Xu Xialing]] from the [[Golden Daggers Club]].
*'''{{WPS|Jeep}}''': Xu utilized a Jeep to make the journey to [[Ta Lo]]. However, due to the bamboo maze guarding the entrance, the Jeep lost control, driving over the edge.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Ten Rings Headquarters]]''': Xu's base of operations was in [[China]]. He also resided at the headquarters with his family until their split. Once [[Ying Li]] died, Xu converted the headquarters back into a training ground for the [[Ten Rings (Organization)|Ten Rings]]. During the [[Expedition to Ta Lo]], Xu forced a reuniting of his family at the headquarters, but when [[Shang-Chi]] and [[Xu Xialing]] refused to help, Xu locked them in the prison.

